name: Bonn's Scary Eight-Legged Beauty
description:
A spider descends from its web on Bonn's Konrad Adenauer bridge over the Rhine river as the sun sets behind the iconic Posttower and bathes the sky in beautiful (and digitally altered) colors.
Although quite small when compared to the size of the picture, the spider catches the beholder's eye as it occupies the picture's geometric center as well as its "color center".
Both the sunset and the spider - a creature feared by most humans - have a profound beauty.
